The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network for active object recognition, which involves selecting the next action to perform on the object with the aim of improving recognition performance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of reinforcement learning and gradient descent for training the network further supports the likelihood of the paper belonging to cs.AI and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The focus on active object recognition also suggests a potential fit with robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
